snippet.title: North Port, Florida
snippet.description: Located in Southwest Florida between Tampa and Fort Myers, the City of North Port is the largest city in Sarasota County. With more than 60,000 residents, North Port boats a median age of 40 that reflects in the communities' vibrant, youthful lifestyle. At 104.1-square-miles and only 20 percent built out, this Florida community is tucked under a thick oak and pine canopy. The natural setting lends itself to a variety of outdoor adventures, including canoeing and kayaking, mountain biking, horse back riding, hiking, bird watching, and more. Easily accessible by Interstate 75, North Port residents are close to the region's pristine beaches and Sarasota County's arts and culture mecca. This vibrant, young community prides itself on being a place where visitors, business owners, and residents can "Achieve Anything." For more information, visit www.CityofNorthPort.com.
